data$N1_avg_corrected<-ifelse(data$N1_LevelDetection=="BLQ", data$N1_LOQ/2, ifelse(data$N1_LevelDetection=="BLD", data$N1_LOD/2, data$N1_avg))

Prepare data

### Count number of N1 N2 assay per filter ###
N1N2.assay.count<-aggregate(N1_avg ~ Sample_ID, subset(data, N1_avg!="NA"), FUN = length)
names(N1N2.assay.count)[2]<-"N1N2_n_assay_per_filter"
data<-as.data.frame(setDT(N1N2.assay.count)[data, on="Sample_ID"])

### Count number of replicate filters per sample ###
filter.count<-aggregate(N1_avg ~ CV + Sample_ID, subset(data, N1_avg!="NA"), FUN = length)
filter.count<-aggregate(N1_avg ~ CV, filter.count, FUN = length)
names(filter.count)[2]<-"n_filter"
data<-as.data.frame(setDT(filter.count)[data, on="CV"])

Day-to-day vs Assay vs filter vs sample variability

Select samples

data.N1N2.comparison<-subset(data, N1N2_n_assay_per_filter>=2 & n_filter>=2 & N1_avg_corrected != "NA")
data.N1N2.comparison<-data.N1N2.comparison[!grepl("slow", data.N1N2.comparison$Sample_ID), ]# remove filters that contain the word "slow"
data.N1N2.comparison$N1c_avg_log10<-log10(data.N1N2.comparison$N1_avg_corrected)

VCA on all data

data.N1N2.comparison.all<-data.N1N2.comparison
count.all<-data.N1N2.comparison %>% group_by(CV) %>% summarize(sum(!is.na(N1c_avg_log10)), .groups = 'drop')
names(count.all)[2]<-"count"
data.N1N2.comparison.all<-as.data.frame(setDT(count.all)[as.data.frame(data.N1N2.comparison.all), on="CV"])

varPlot(form=N1c_avg_log10~City/CV/Sample_ID, Data=as.data.frame(subset(data.N1N2.comparison.all, count==4)))

fit.all <- anovaVCA(N1c_avg_log10~City/CV/Sample_ID, as.data.frame(subset(data.N1N2.comparison.all, count==4)))
print(fit.all, digits=2)

VCA only on quantitative data

data.N1N2.comparison.q<-subset(data.N1N2.comparison, N1_LevelDetection=="Quantifiable")

count.q<-data.N1N2.comparison.q %>% group_by(CV) %>% summarize(sum(!is.na(N1c_avg_log10)), .groups = 'drop')
names(count.q)[2]<-"count"
data.N1N2.comparison.q<-as.data.frame(setDT(count.q)[as.data.frame(data.N1N2.comparison.q), on="CV"])

varPlot(form=N1c_avg_log10~City/CV/Sample_ID, Data=as.data.frame(subset(data.N1N2.comparison.q, count==4)))

fit.q <- anovaVCA(N1c_avg_log10~City/CV/Sample_ID, as.data.frame(subset(data.N1N2.comparison.q, count==4)))
print(fit.q, digits=2)

#rename variables for the paper
data.N1N2.comparison.q <- data.N1N2.comparison.q[order(data.N1N2.comparison.q$CV),]
data.N1N2.comparison.q$WWTP<-data.N1N2.comparison.q$City
data.N1N2.comparison.q$Sample<-data.N1N2.comparison.q$CV
data.N1N2.comparison.q$Filter<-data.N1N2.comparison.q$Sample_ID
data.N1N2.comparison.q$Filter<-ifelse(grepl("-1", data.N1N2.comparison.q$Sample_ID), "a", "b")
varPlot(form=N1c_avg_log10~WWTP/Sample/Filter,
        keep.order = TRUE,
        #VarLab = list(cex = 0.5 , adj = c(0.5, 0.5)),
        Data=as.data.frame(subset(data.N1N2.comparison.q, count==4)), 
        YLabel = list(cex=1.3, line = 3, text = "N1 concentration  (log10 - cp/L)"))
